This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it proposes a hybrid differential evolution algorithm to automatically design the architectures of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification. Additionally, the paper focuses on the optimization of hyperparameters, which is a common task in neural network design. The paper also belongs to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image classification using CNNs. The paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it involves the use of machine learning techniques to design CNNs. The Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also likely as the paper deals with the automation of a task that would otherwise require human expertise. Finally, the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category may be relevant as the proposed algorithm involves the optimization of a complex system (CNN architecture) using evolutionary computation.
